  <p>To install Wazuh with Docker Compose, clone the official repository, run <code>docker-compose up -d</code> and in minutes you'll have the three components up: Indexer, Server and Dashboard. You only need Docker and Docker Compose installed on the server.</p>

  <h2>How to install Wazuh with Docker Compose step by step?</h2>

  <p>
    In this guide I'll show you <strong>how to install Wazuh using Docker Compose</strong>, one of the fastest and simplest ways to deploy the full environment. With just 4 commands you'll have Wazuh running with all its components: Indexer, Server and Dashboard.
  </p>

