  <h2>Why should you use Docker for Wazuh?</h2>

  <p>
    Docker offers several advantages for deploying Wazuh:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Speed:</strong> The full environment is ready in minutes</li>
    <li><strong>Portability:</strong> It works the same on any system with Docker installed</li>
    <li><strong>Isolation:</strong> The containers don't interfere with other system services</li>
    <li><strong>Easy upgrades:</strong> Changing version is as simple as editing the tag</li>
    <li><strong>Ideal for testing:</strong> Perfect for labs and development environments</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What do you need before you start?</h2>

  <p>
    Before you start, you need to have installed:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Docker</strong> (version 20.10 or higher)</li>
    <li><strong>Docker Compose</strong> (version 2.0 or higher)</li>
    <li><strong>Git</strong> to clone the repository</li>
  </ul>

